  "prompt": "How does one configure TCS mail on an iPhone?",
  "response": "Configuring TCS (Tata Consultancy Services) mail on an iPhone typically involves using the default Mail app and setting up an Exchange account. Here's a step-by-step guide:\n\n**Prerequisites:**\n\n*   **TCS Email Address:** You'll need your full TCS email address (e.g., yourname@tcs.com).\n*   **TCS Email Password:** You'll need your TCS email password.\n*   **Server Information (Recommended):** While the iPhone can often auto-discover settings, having the specific server information can help ensure a successful setup. Obtain this information from your TCS IT support or internal documentation.  Common settings include:\n    *   **Server:** Usually, it will be `outlook.office365.com` (or a similar Microsoft Exchange server address)\n    *   **Domain:** Often, this is your company's domain name within TCS, e.g., `tcs.com`. (sometimes left blank if using UPN)\n    *   **Username:** Your full TCS email address (e.g., yourname@tcs.com).\n    *   **Port:** Typically, 443 (for SSL).\n    *   **Use SSL:** Enabled/Checked.\n\n**Steps to Configure TCS Mail on iPhone:**\n\n1.  **Open the Settings App:**  Find and tap the \"Settings\" app on your iPhone's home screen.\n\n2.  **Go to Mail:** Scroll down and tap on \"Mail.\"\n\n3.  **Add Account:**  Tap on \"Accounts.\"  If you already have accounts set up, you'll see them listed here. Tap \"Add Account.\"\n\n4.  **Choose Exchange:**  From the list of account providers, select \"Microsoft Exchange.\"  *Do not select Outlook.com*.\n\n5.  **Enter Email Address:**  Enter your full TCS email address (e.g., yourname@tcs.com) in the \"Email\" field. You might see a prompt asking you to \"Configure Manually\" or \"Sign In\". If you see **\"Sign In\"**, tap on that and it will take you to the Microsoft login page for your TCS email.  Follow the on-screen instructions to authenticate.  If you see **\"Configure Manually\"** proceed to the next step.\n\n6.  **Configure Manually (If prompted or if auto-discovery fails):**\n    *   Tap \"Configure Manually\" (if available)\n    *   You may be asked what type of account to setup. Select \"Exchange\".\n    *   Enter the following information:\n        *   **Email:** Your full TCS email address.\n        *   **Server:** `outlook.office365.com` (or the specific server address provided by TCS IT support).\n        *   **Domain:**  `tcs.com` (or the domain specified by TCS IT support. Often, this can be left blank if you are using your full email address as the username or User Principal Name (UPN))\n        *   **Username:** Your full TCS email address.\n        *   **Password:** Your TCS email password.\n        *   **Description:**  A name for the account (e.g., \"TCS Mail\").\n    *   Tap \"Next.\"  The iPhone will attempt to verify the account settings.\n\n7.  **Verify and Choose Services to Sync:** If the settings are correct, the iPhone will connect to the Exchange server. You'll then be prompted to choose which services you want to sync (Mail, Contacts, Calendars, Reminders, Notes). Select the services you need and toggle them on or off.\n\n8.  **Save the Account:**  Tap \"Save\" to save the account configuration.\n\n**Troubleshooting:**\n\n*   **Incorrect Password:**  Double-check that you've entered your TCS email password correctly.  Passwords are case-sensitive.\n*   **Incorrect Server Settings:**  Verify the server address, domain, and other server settings with your TCS IT support.  Using the wrong settings will prevent the account from connecting.\n*   **SSL/TLS Issues:**  Make sure SSL/TLS is enabled (usually the default) and the port is correct (usually 443).\n*   **Two-Factor Authentication (2FA):**  If your TCS account is configured for two-factor authentication, you may need to generate an app-specific password or use the Microsoft Authenticator app.  Consult your TCS IT support for guidance.  Modern Authentication should support 2FA without an app-specific password if configured properly by TCS IT.\n*   **Account Restrictions:**  Your TCS IT department may have policies in place that restrict email access on mobile devices.  Contact them to ensure your device is authorized.\n*   **Profile Required:** Some companies, including TCS, require you to install a profile to get your email to work. Ask your IT support if a profile is required.\n\n**Important Considerations:**\n\n*   **Security:** Ensure your iPhone has a strong passcode enabled. Mobile devices are vulnerable to theft, and access to your email account could compromise sensitive information.\n*   **Data Usage:**  Syncing email, contacts, and calendars over a cellular network can consume data. Be mindful of your data plan limits. Consider using Wi-Fi whenever possible.\n*   **Corporate Policies:**  Be aware of TCS's policies regarding email usage on personal devices.  You may be required to adhere to certain security standards or data retention policies.\n\nBy following these steps and consulting your TCS IT support if needed, you should be able to successfully configure your TCS email on your iPhone. Remember to prioritize security and adhere to your company's IT policies.\n",
